---
id: org.dxos.echo
name: Echo
version: 0.10.0
---

`@dxos/echo` is the public API surface for ECHO — the typed, local-first object
graph backed by Automerge. It defines schema (types and relations), the object
data model, references, query/filter, and the Effect `Database` service. Client
wiring (`EchoClient`, `EchoHost`, sync, hypergraph implementation) lives in
`@dxos/echo-db`; React hooks (`useQuery`, `useObject`, `useSchema`) live in
`@dxos/echo-react`.

This spec captures the package's namespace modules and their public API, plus the
features and acceptance criteria that constrain them.

Every module is an ESM namespace module following the DXOS namespace-module
styleguide: a PascalCase file in `src/`, re-exported from `index.ts` as
`export * as <Name> from './<Name>'`, and consumed by callers as a namespace
(`Obj.make`, `Filter.eq` — never a bare `makeObj`). Members are unprefixed; the
caller always reads `<Name>.<member>`. Each module has a matching subpath
entrypoint (`@dxos/echo/Filter`) for narrow imports. `DXN`, `EID`, `URI` (from
`@dxos/keys`) and `QueryAST` (from `@dxos/echo-protocol`) are re-exported at the
root.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term     | URI                       |
| -------- | ------------------------- |
| `module` | `org.dxos.mdl.module@1.0` |
| `feat`   | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`   |
| `test`   | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`   |

## Modules

### Core modeling

```mdl
module Type
  desc: |
    Schema definition and introspection. A single class-based declaration unifies
    the runtime schema entity and the TypeScript instance type. The DXN comes
    first, the schema is applied to the returned function.
  api:
    makeObject: <Self>(dxn, opts?) => (schema) => ObjClass   # declare an object type.
    makeRelation: <Self>(dxn) => ({ source, target, id? }) => (schema) => RelationClass  # declare a relation type.
    makeObjectFromJsonSchema: (jsonSchema) => AnyObj         # build an object type from JSON Schema.
    makeRelationFromJsonSchema: (jsonSchema) => AnyRelation  # build a relation type from JSON Schema.
    AnyObj / AnyRelation / AnyType / AnyEntity: type         # wildcard schema bounds.
    InstanceType: <typeof X> => T                            # instance type of a schema (or use the class name).
    getURI: (schema) => DXN                                  # type DXN, e.g. dxn:type:example.com/type/Person:0.1.0.
    getTypename: (schema) => string                          # typename portion of the type DXN.
    getVersion: (schema) => string                           # semantic version of the type.
    getMeta: (schema) => Meta                                # type metadata (icon, color, ...).
    isObject / isRelation / isType / isMutable: (x) => boolean  # predicates.
```

```mdl
module Obj
  desc: |
    The runtime data API for objects. Functions work on objects both inside and
    outside a database, so most getters can return undefined.
  api:
    make: (Type, props) => Obj                    # create an instance; props typed via MakeProps.
    Unknown / Any: schema | type                  # untyped object schema / instance type.
    MakeProps: <typeof T> => props                # props accepted by make for a type.
    isObject: (x) => boolean                      # is this an ECHO object.
    instanceOf: (Type, obj) => boolean            # is obj an instance of Type.
    isDeleted: (obj) => boolean                   # tombstone marker.
    getSchema: (obj) => Schema | undefined        # resolved schema, if available.
    getDXN: (obj) => DXN                           # DXN of the object itself (dxn:echo:...).
    getTypename / getTypeURI: (obj) => ...        # type identity of the instance.
    getMeta: (obj) => Meta                        # object metadata section (keys, ...).
    getSnapshot / snapshotOf: (obj) => Snapshot   # immutable point-in-time copy.
    clone: (obj, opts?) => Obj                    # structural copy.
    getValue / setValue / update: (obj, path, ..) # path-based read / write / mutation.
    subscribe: (obj, cb) => Unsubscribe           # react to changes on a live object.
    toJSON: (obj) => Json                          # serialize.
    fromJSON: (json, { graph, db }) => Obj        # deserialize into a graph / db.
    Meta / ID: symbol | accessor                  # reserved-field symbols and accessors.
```

```mdl
module Relation
  desc: |
    Relation instances. Relations extend objects with typed source / target
    endpoints addressed by reserved symbol keys.
  api:
    make: (Type, props) => Relation               # create a relation (endpoints via Source / Target).
    Source / Target: unique symbol                # reserved endpoint keys.
    getSource / getTarget: (rel) => Obj           # resolved endpoint objects.
    getSourceURI / getTargetURI: (rel) => DXN     # endpoint DXNs.
    isRelation: (x) => boolean                    # predicate.
    instanceOf: (Type, rel) => boolean            # is rel an instance of Type.
    Unknown: schema                               # untyped relation.
    getMeta / getValue / setValue / update / subscribe: ...  # shared object surface.
```

```mdl
module Ref
  desc: References between entities, stored as `{ "/": "dxn:..." }` and resolved lazily.
  api:
    Ref: (Schema) => RefSchema        # schema for a typed reference field.
    Array: (Schema) => Schema         # schema for an array of refs.
    make: (obj) => Ref                # ref to an existing object.
    fromURI: (dxn) => Ref             # ref from a DXN.
    isRef: (x) => boolean             # predicate.
    hasEntityId / isRefType: ...      # predicates.
    Target: <R> => T                  # target instance type of a ref.
    Resolver: interface               # resolves a ref to its target.
```

```mdl
module Entity
  desc: The shared substrate for objects and relations.
  api:
    Kind: { Object, Relation }        # entity-kind discriminator.
    Unknown / Any: schema | type      # untyped entity.
    isEntity: (x) => boolean          # predicate.
    instanceOf: (Type, entity) => boolean  # kind-agnostic instance check.
    isSnapshot: (x) => boolean        # predicate.
```

### Query

```mdl
module Query
  desc: Graph-shaped selections compiled to a QueryAST.
  api:
    select: (filter) => Query         # objects matching a filter.
    type: (Type, props?) => Query     # objects of a type (optionally filtered).
    from: (source) => Query           # start a query from a source set.
    all: () => Query                  # everything.
    without: (query) => Query         # set difference.
    fromAst: (ast) => Query           # build from a raw QueryAST.
    pretty: (query) => string         # human-readable form.
    Any: type                         # wildcard query type.
    Type: <Q> => T                    # element type extracted from a query.
```

```mdl
module Filter
  desc: Predicate builders composed into queries.
  api:
    type: (Type) => Filter            # match by type.
    props: (shape) => Filter          # match by property shape.
    id: (id | id[]) => Filter         # match by object id.
    tag / key / foreignKeys: ...      # match by tag / meta key / foreign keys.
    text: (query, opts?) => Filter    # full-text search.
    eq / neq / gt / gte / lt / lte: (value) => Filter  # comparators.
    contains / between / childOf: ... # membership / range / hierarchy.
    created / updated: (range) => Filter  # time predicates.
    not: (filter) => Filter           # negation.
    everything / nothing: Filter      # identity / empty.
    Any: type                         # wildcard filter type.
```

```mdl
module QueryResult
  desc: The handle returned by db.query(...).
  api:
    run: () => Promise<Results>       # one-shot execution.
    subscribe: (cb) => Unsubscribe    # reactive subscription to result changes.
```

```mdl
module Order
  desc: Result ordering.
  api:
    natural: Order                    # insertion / natural order.
    property: (path) => Order         # order by a property path.
    rank: Order                       # order by rank.
    created / updated: Order          # order by timestamps.
    Any: type                         # wildcard order type.
```

```mdl
module Aggregate
  desc: Grouping and reduction over query results.
  api:
    group: (spec) => Aggregate        # group rows by a key.
    count: () => Aggregate            # count rows.
    min / max: (path) => Aggregate    # extrema over a property.
    items: () => Aggregate            # collect matched items.
    Spec / AggregationResult: type    # spec and result shapes.
```

### Database access (Effect)

```mdl
module Database
  desc: |
    The imperative `Database` interface plus the Effect surface. The interface
    exposes add / remove / query / getObjectById / makeRef / flush / graph /
    schemaRegistry. The Effect functions require Database.Service in context.
  api:
    Database: interface               # imperative DB handle.
    Service: Context.Tag              # yield* Database.Service => { db }.
    layer: (db) => Layer              # provide the service from an imperative db.
    notAvailable: Layer               # stub layer that fails on use.
    makeService: (db) => Service      # construct the service value.
    query: (filterOrQuery) => Effect  # query within the service (.run to execute).
    runQuery: (filterOrQuery) => Effect  # query and collect results.
    schemaQuery / runSchemaQuery: ... # schema-registry queries.
    add / remove / flush: (...) => Effect  # mutations and persistence.
    resolve: (dxn | ref) => Effect    # resolve via the graph.
    load: (ref) => Effect             # load a ref target; does not require Service.
    spaceId: () => Effect             # space id of the current db.
    isDatabase: (x) => boolean        # predicate.
```

```mdl
module Registry
  desc: Schema registry — registers and resolves ECHO types.
  api:
    Registry: interface               # registry handle.
    Service: Context.Tag              # Effect service for the registry.
    runQuery: (query) => Effect       # query registered schema.
    isRegistry: (x) => boolean        # predicate.
```

```mdl
module Hypergraph
  desc: The cross-space object graph that resolves refs across spaces.
  api:
    Hypergraph: interface             # extends Database.Queryable; resolves refs.
    RefResolutionContext: interface   # context for resolving a ref.
    RefResolverOptions: interface     # options controlling resolution.
```

```mdl
module Scope
  desc: Ambient resolution scopes.
  api:
    space: Scope                      # resolve within a space.
    registry: Scope                   # resolve within the schema registry.
    feed: Scope                       # resolve within a feed.
```

```mdl
module Migration
  desc: Object-level schema migrations.
  api:
    define: (spec) => ObjectMigration  # declare a migration between type versions.
    ObjectMigration: type              # a migration definition.
    ObjectMigrationContext: type       # runtime context passed to a migration.
    TransformResult: <To> => type      # result of a transform step.
```

### Values, formats & serialization

```mdl
module Text
  desc: Collaborative text edits over a key path.
  api:
    update: (obj, path, text) => void  # replace text at a path.
    splice: (obj, path, edit) => void  # apply a splice edit.
    apply: (obj, path, edit) => void   # apply an Edit.
    KeyPath / Edit: type               # path and edit shapes.
```

```mdl
module Blob
  desc: Binary attachments with inline or external storage.
  api:
    Blob: objectType                   # the Blob object type (org.dxos.type.blob).
    make: (props) => Blob              # create a blob.
    inlineData / externalData: (...) => BlobData  # inline vs external payloads.
    fromBytes: (bytes, opts?) => Blob  # build from raw bytes.
    read: (blob) => Promise<bytes>     # read payload.
    exists: (blob) => Promise<boolean> # availability check.
    url: (blob) => string              # resolvable URL.
    MAX_INLINE_SIZE: number            # inline payload ceiling.
    Storage / Scheme: enum             # storage backend and scheme.
```

```mdl
module Format
  desc: Format schemas for typed scalar values.
  api:
    string / number / date / object / select: schema  # formatted value schemas.
```

```mdl
module Annotation
  desc: Attach metadata (icons, colors, formats) to schema.
  api:
    make: (props) => Annotation        # define an annotation.
    get / set / update: (...) => ...   # read / write an annotation on schema.
    getFromAst: (ast) => value         # read from a schema AST.
    atom / atomProperty: ...           # atom-level annotation helpers.
    Dictionary: schema                 # dictionary annotation value.
    getDictionary / setDictionary / buildDictionary: ...  # dictionary helpers.
```

```mdl
module Json
  desc: JSON serialization helpers.
  api:
    createRefReplacer: (opts) => JsonReplacer  # ref-aware JSON.stringify replacer.
```

```mdl
module JsonSchema
  desc: Bridge between Effect Schema and JSON Schema.
  api:
    toEffectSchema: (jsonSchema) => Schema  # JSON Schema -> Effect Schema.
    toJsonSchema: (schema) => JsonSchema    # Effect Schema -> JSON Schema.
    JsonSchema: schema                      # the JSON Schema type.
```

```mdl
module Key
  desc: Identifier types re-exported for convenience.
  api:
    EntityId / SpaceId / EID / URI: type   # identifier types.
    ForeignKey: type                        # external system key.
```

### Built-in types

```mdl
module Collection
  desc: A named, ordered list of refs.
  api:
    Collection: objectType             # org.dxos.type.collection.
    make: (props) => Collection        # create a collection.
    isCollection: (x) => boolean       # predicate.
```

```mdl
module Feed
  desc: An append-only feed object with cursors, sync, and retention.
  api:
    Feed: objectType                   # org.dxos.type.feed.
    make: (props) => Feed              # create a feed.
    append / remove: (feed, item) => Effect  # mutate the feed.
    query: (feed, ...) => ...          # read entries.
    sync / getSyncState: (...) => ...  # replication control and state.
    cursor / next / nextOption: ...    # cursor navigation.
    setRetention: (feed, opts) => void # retention policy.
    getFeedUri: (feed) => URI          # feed URI.
```

```mdl
module Tag
  desc: A label object plus list helpers.
  api:
    Tag: objectType                    # the Tag type.
    make: (props) => Tag               # create a tag.
    findOrCreate: (list, label) => Tag # idempotent lookup / create.
    findTagByLabel: (list, label) => Tag | undefined  # lookup.
    sortTags / createTagList: ...      # ordering and list construction.
    Map: type                          # tag map shape.
```

```mdl
module View
  desc: A projection over data with field-schema helpers.
  api:
    View: objectType                   # org.dxos.type.view.
    make: (props) => View              # create a view.
    Projection: type                   # projection descriptor.
    FieldSchema / FieldType: schema | type  # field descriptors.
    createFieldId: (...) => string     # stable field id.
    KeyValueProps: schema              # key/value field props.
```

```mdl
module Dataset
  desc: A dataset value type.
  api:
    Dataset: type                      # dataset shape.
    isDataset: (x) => boolean          # predicate.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Namespace-module API surface

  req F-1.1:
    when: a caller imports @dxos/echo
    then: every public module is available as an unprefixed namespace
          (Obj.make, Filter.eq), and each is also importable via its subpath
          (@dxos/echo/Filter)

  req F-1.2:
    when: a caller needs identifiers or the query AST
    then: DXN / EID / URI (from @dxos/keys) and QueryAST (from @dxos/echo-protocol)
          are re-exported at the package root
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Type declaration

  req F-2.1:
    when: a named, reusable type is declared
    then: `class X extends Type.makeObject<X>(dxn)(schema) {}` yields both the
          runtime schema entity (via static members) and the TypeScript instance
          type X, with no separate `type`/`interface` alias

  req F-2.2:
    when: a relation type is declared
    then: `Type.makeRelation<X>(dxn)({ source, target })(schema)` binds typed
          source and target endpoints

  req F-2.3:
    when: a schema is introspected
    then: Type.getURI / getTypename / getVersion / getMeta return its identity and
          metadata
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Object data model

  req F-3.1:
    when: Obj.make(Type, props) is called
    then: an object is created carrying id, type DXN, and (when resolvable) schema

  req F-3.2:
    when: a field on a live object is mutated in place
    then: Obj.subscribe listeners fire and query subscriptions re-evaluate

  req F-3.3:
    when: an accessor is called on an object outside a database
    then: it returns undefined rather than throwing where identity cannot be resolved

  req F-3.4:
    when: an object is serialized and deserialized
    then: Obj.toJSON / fromJSON round-trip its id, type, meta, and refs
```

```mdl
feat F-4: References

  req F-4.1:
    when: a ref field is declared with Ref.Ref(Schema)
    then: it stores a DXN and resolves lazily to a target of the schema type

  req F-4.2:
    when: a ref target is loaded in Effect code
    then: Database.load resolves it, and a missing target surfaces as
          EntityNotFoundError (catchable by tag)
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Query and filter

  req F-5.1:
    when: db.query(filterOrQuery) is called
    then: a QueryResult is returned exposing .run() (one-shot) and .subscribe()
          (reactive)

  req F-5.2:
    when: a filter is composed from Filter builders
    then: type, props, id, tag, text, comparators, time, and boolean combinators
          compile to a single QueryAST

  req F-5.3:
    when: results are ordered or aggregated
    then: Order and Aggregate modifiers apply over the matched set
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Effect Database service

  req F-6.1:
    when: Effect code declares Database.Service
    then: Database.query / add / remove / flush / resolve compose as Effects that
          require the service

  req F-6.2:
    when: an imperative db is bridged into Effect code
    then: Database.layer(db) provides the service, and Database.notAvailable stubs
          it for contexts without a db
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Class type is both schema and TS type
  given: `class Person extends Type.makeObject<Person>(dxn)(Schema.Struct({ name: Schema.String })) {}`
  then:
    - Type.getTypename(Person) equals the typename encoded in dxn
    - Obj.make(Person, { name: 'Bill' }) is assignable to Person
    - Obj.instanceOf(Person, obj) is true for that object
```

```mdl
test T-2: Object round-trips through JSON
  given: an object created with Obj.make and added to a db
  when: it is passed through Obj.toJSON then Obj.fromJSON({ graph, db })
  then:
    - id, type DXN, and meta are preserved
    - ref fields resolve to the same targets
```

```mdl
test T-3: Query subscription reacts to mutation
  given: a subscribed QueryResult for Filter.type(Person)
  when: a new Person is added and an existing one is mutated
  then:
    - the subscription fires with the updated result set
    - a one-shot .run() returns the same set
```

```mdl
test T-4: Effect query requires the service
  given: an Effect program using Database.query(Filter.everything)
  when: run without providing Database.Service
  then: the program is a type error / fails to run until Database.layer(db) is provided
```

```mdl
test T-5: Missing ref target is catchable
  given: a ref whose target does not exist
  when: Database.load(ref) runs
  then: it fails with EntityNotFoundError, catchable via Effect.catchTag('EntityNotFoundError', ...)
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext module
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.module@1.0
  desc: |
    An ESM namespace module following the DXOS namespace-module styleguide:
    a PascalCase file in src/, re-exported from index.ts as
    `export * as <Name> from './<Name>'`. Callers import it as a namespace, so
    members are unprefixed (`Obj.make`, not `makeObj`). The file path is inferred
    from the block name (`Obj` -> `src/Obj.ts`).
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    api: ApiMap         # public members reached as `<Name>.<member>`  (name: TypeExpr # comment)
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```
